TWO people have been killed in separate accidents, including a villager from Kalemba in Ngara District, who was struck by lightning on Monday, this week. Kagera Regional Police Commander (RPC) Revocatus Malimi named the victim as Mr Robert Jacob (35), adding that during the incident two other family members were also injured by lightning: Byamungu Jacob (14), a Standard Three pupil at Murukukumbo Primary School and Mr Mapinduzi Jacob (25). Both are admitted to Rulenge Mission Hospital and their health is improving. The RPC also said Mr Paul Nyerere (28) from Kalenge Village in Biharamulo District was killed on the spot as the pit he was extracting sand from collapsed. 